args: The wound is not mortal, but I can't\ntake firm strides with this leg.\nI fear I may only slow you down.
LADY, LADY, SHE'S OUR MAN!\nIF SHE CAN'T DO IT, NO ONE CAN!
What in heaven's name? Who are you?
You gotta believe! Believe in YOURSELF!\nNow get out there and WIN, wooooo!
I haven't the faintest idea who this\nwoman is, yet somehow her cheering\nhas filled me with renewed energy!
She is correct—I CAN do this!\nNow take this, fiend! Hallowed Waters!
Yaaay, you did it! I'm so glad I could help!
You were indeed of great assistance.\nBut if I may, who ARE you?
I'm Emma—a receptionist and cheerleader\nfrom Apollonia. Nice to meetcha!
Apollonia? That's the city known\nfor its battle colosseum.
Yep! People come from far and wide to\ncompete with swords, fists, spears...you\nname it!
So what brings ya all the way out here?
Well, I'm here to meet somebody\ncalled ＂the Prince of the Halidom.＂\nDon't suppose you know him?
Er, that would be me, actually.
Wait, for seriously? You are LITERALLY\nthe first person I've asked about this.\nTalk about lucky, right?
Welp, since you're standing here, I was\nhoping to join your team! Er, or your\narmy or league or...whatever you have.
See, my mission in life is to raise\npeople's spirits with my cheering.
And what better way to do that than\nto come and join the prince who's\nout there fighting for everyone?
That's a pretty weird life mission.
It is not! ...Sooo can I join or what?
I am having some difficulty seeing how\nsuch a talent will be of practical use.
Yeah, but I don't want to turn her down.\nI mean, what if it's actually helpful?
Maybe we can consider you on something\nof a trial basis. Would that be all right?
Oooo, like a test? Or a QUEST?!\nYou're on! I'll totally prove my worth!
After reaching the castle, Emma set about\nencouraging people in the surrounding villages\nin every way she could.
Waaaah! I don't wanna eat my veggies!
WE LOVE VEGGIES, YES WE DO!\nWE LOVE VEGGIES, HOW 'BOUT YOU?!

Now look, I know veggies can be bitter
and slimy and gross, but that just means
you're SUPER tough for eating them!
Now come on. Try one bite. Pleeeease?
Yeah, okay. *nibble* Hey, that wasn't\nas bad as I thought! *munch* *crunch*
*sniff* Aw, I'll never get the hang of\nthis stupid gymnastics routine!
But what if I sing you a special song?!
Front leg, BOOM! Back leg, WHOA!\nElbows tight and 'ROUND YOU GOOOO!
Now you try it! Oh, but don't forget\nthe song while you do it.
O-okay. Um...front leg boom,\nback leg...whoa? Elboooows...
Hey, I did it! Thanks, lady!
Hurrrk! M'poor back's so sore I can't even\nmove! Guess I'll never see m'wife again...
What you need is to exercise—and what\nyou need to exercise is MUSIC! Reaaady?

Take a step forward, then breathe in!
Stretch that back and win, win, win!
If you get sweaty, don't have a cow!
Just take a cloth and mop your brow!
...My stars and garters, I can move.\nI can moooooove!
Just you wait, honeylumps—I'm gonna\nrun across hill and dale to find ya!
Emma's cheerleading is going quite well.
I have heard the same. It seems her\nclaims about being able to encourage\npeople were true after all.
The castle AND surrounding area have\nbecome much livelier since Emma came.
Of course, I was convinced the moment\nshe cheered me on during that battle.
Maybe we oughta rein in all'a this\nenthusiasm a bit. Though I'll admit\nshe doesn't seem a bad gal.
...What's that?! Someone's feeling down in\nthe next village? This will not stand—no\none is allowed to be glum on my watch!
I'll be back, Prince. I gotta run over to the\nnext village and cheer up a grumpy gus!
Er, okay? Take care, I guess.
Heh. I think this new recruit is really\ngoing to help keep our spirits high.
